This paper is primarily focused on deep learning and neural networks, which suggests that it would likely fall under the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the performance of these networks on image classification tasks, which could also place it in the cs.CV (Computer Vision) sub-category. The use of theoretical guarantees and analysis of expressivity could also suggest the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of structured matrices, which could place it in the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. Finally, the use of a real-world video classification dataset could suggest the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category.
